## How to Run the Project

This project is run in four main phases:

1. Provision GCP infrastructure with Terraform
2. Load station dimension data with Dataproc PySpark
3. Land simulated trip events and process them with PySpark Structured Streaming
4. Build gold marts with Dataform

All commands below are run from the project root unless stated otherwise.

---

### 1. Set environment variables

```bash
export PROJECT_ID="project-bd4d8f5"
export REGION="us-central1"
export ENV="dev"

export RAW_BUCKET="${PROJECT_ID}-bike-share-raw-${ENV}"
export TEMP_BUCKET="${PROJECT_ID}-bike-share-temp-${ENV}"

export DATAPROC_CLUSTER="bike-share-spark-cluster"

export SILVER_DATASET="bike_silver"
export GOLD_DATASET="bike_gold"

export DATAFORM_REPO="bike-share-dataform-repo"
export DATAFORM_WORKFLOW_CONFIG="bike-share-gold-workflow"


gcloud config set project $PROJECT_ID

gcloud auth login

cd infra

terraform init
terraform fmt -recursive
terraform validate
terraform plan -out=tfplan
terraform apply tfplan

cd ../..
```
### This provisions the main GCP resources, including:

- Cloud Storage buckets
- BigQuery datasets
- Dataproc cluster
- Service accounts and IAM
- Dataform repository resources
- Network resources

#### Confirm the station CSV was uploaded to Cloud Storage:

```bash
gsutil ls gs://$RAW_BUCKET/raw/stations/stations.csv
```

### Build the station dimension table
```bash
gcloud dataproc jobs submit pyspark dataproc/jobs/build_dim_station.py \
  --cluster $DATAPROC_CLUSTER \
  --region $REGION \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  -- \
  --project-id $PROJECT_ID \
  --station-path gs://$RAW_BUCKET/raw/stations/stations.csv \
  --silver-dataset $SILVER_DATASET \
  --temp-bucket $TEMP_BUCKET
```


### Generate simulated trip events
```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install google-cloud-storage
```
#### Generate fake bike trip events into the Cloud Storage raw trip landing path:
```bash
python producers/fake_trip_stream.py \
  --station-file sample_data/stations/stations.csv \
  --bucket $RAW_BUCKET \
  --prefix raw/trips \
  --events-per-batch 25 \
  --sleep-seconds 10 \
  --max-batches 10
```

### Process trip events with PySpark Structured Streaming

```bash
gcloud dataproc jobs submit pyspark dataproc/jobs/stream_fact_trip_from_gcs.py \
  --cluster $DATAPROC_CLUSTER \
  --region $REGION \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  -- \
  --project-id $PROJECT_ID \
  --input-path gs://$RAW_BUCKET/raw/trips/ \
  --checkpoint-path gs://$TEMP_BUCKET/checkpoints/fact_trip_v1 \
  --silver-dataset $SILVER_DATASET \
  --temp-bucket $TEMP_BUCKET \
  --trigger-once
```

#### Process continuous mode
```bash
gcloud dataproc jobs submit pyspark dataproc/jobs/stream_fact_trip_from_gcs.py \
  --cluster $DATAPROC_CLUSTER \
  --region $REGION \
  --project $PROJECT_ID \
  --async \
  -- \
  --project-id $PROJECT_ID \
  --input-path gs://$RAW_BUCKET/raw/trips/ \
  --checkpoint-path gs://$TEMP_BUCKET/checkpoints/fact_trip_continuous \
  --silver-dataset $SILVER_DATASET \
  --temp-bucket $TEMP_BUCKET \
  --processing-time "30 seconds"
```